Data Processing Example

ROBIN Network

2022-06-28

Plan

Insert text explaining the main steps of the ROBIN pipeline.

  • Data format (columns: Agency, Station, Day, Flow, Flag)
  • Check for Level-1/Level-2 status based on completeness.
  • Summary statistics
    • Monthly thresholds
    • POT series
    • 30-day/10-day/7-day rolling totals
    • Annual/monthly/quarterly quantiles/mean
    • Annual 1-day/10-day/30-day maxima
    • Annual 7-day/30-day minima
  • Tests
    • Pettitt breakpoint test
    • Seasonal Mann-Kendall
    • Rolling Mann-Kendall-Snyers Indicators
  • SSI
  • Intermittence
  • Mean Annual Flow (Standardised)
  • Aridity Index

Read in data

First the data must be read in, hopefully in the pre-specified format. The only addition required is the addition of any other flags to the Flag field. Currently there are:

  • M: Missing value. Should correspond to an NA, 0, or empty value "" in the Value column.
  • E: Estimated (or modelled) value
  • S: Suspect value, may have high associated error.

Dates should be consistent, either with a full date (e.g.2022-04-01), or a full date and time (e.g.2022-04-01T09:00:00Z)

filein_path <- "./41022_gdf.csv"
date_format <- "date" # state "date" or "datetime"

data_in <- read_in_robin(filein_path, skip=21)
## Warning in read.table(file = file, header = header, sep = sep, quote = quote, :
## header and 'col.names' are of different lengths
data_in$Agency <- "EA"
data_in$Station <- 41022

Check data type

All the data should be gauged daily flow.

check_for_level(data_in, "M")
## [1] "Suitable for trend analysis"
## $stationLevel
## [1] 1
## 
## $trendFlag
## [1] TRUE

Reformat data

Dates are reformatted into a datetime variable, and a numerical record ordering is added. QA flags are converted to a factor form. Data without issue should have empty QA_Flag fields.

data_in$id <- seq(1, nrow(data_in)) # does not account for missing rows in the data
data_in$Flag <- factor(data_in$Flag)

# Make the lfstat object
lf_flow <- data_in
DAY <- lf_flow$Day
lf_flow$day <- lubridate::day(lf_flow$Day)
lf_flow$month <- lubridate::month(lf_flow$Day)
lf_flow$year <- lubridate::year(lf_flow$Day)
lf_flow$flow <- lf_flow$Flow
lf_flow <- lf_flow[,c("day", "month", "year", "flow")]

year_start_month <- 10
lf_flow <- lfstat::createlfobj(lf_flow, hyearstart=year_start_month)
lf_flow$date <- DAY

Derive flow statistics

High Flow

AMAX

MIN_DAYS_PER_YEAR <- 300 # Need to agree on.
data_in$year <- lubridate::year(data_in$Day)
amax_raw <- data_in %>%
  group_by(year) %>%
  summarise(count=n(), amax=max(Flow, na.rm=T), doy=which.max(Flow)) %>% 
  dplyr::filter(count > MIN_DAYS_PER_YEAR)

plot(amax_raw$year, amax_raw$amax, type='p', col=2, log='y')

Peaks-over-Threshold

vmt_pot <- lfstat::vary_threshold(lf_flow,
                      varying="monthly",
                      fun=function(x){quantile(x, probs=c(0.986))})
## Warning in as.xts.lfobj(x): No unit found in attributes, assuming 'm/s'.
## Use flowunit(x) <- "l/s" to define the flow unit. See help(flowunit).
lf_flow$threshold <- as.vector(vmt_pot)

vmt_summary <- lf_flow %>% group_by(month) %>% summarise(threshold=mean(threshold))

peaks <- ilaprosUtils::extractPeaks(vecObs=lf_flow$flow)
pots <- lf_flow[((lf_flow$flow > lf_flow$threshold) & (peaks==1)), ]
plot(lf_flow$date, lf_flow$flow, col="grey80", type='l', xlab="Date", ylab="Flow")
points(pots$date, pots$flow, col=2)

Low flow

Percentiles of flow

flow_quantiles <- lfstat::Qxx(lf_flow, c(5, 70, 90, 95))
yearly_quantiles <- lfstat::Qxx(lf_flow, c(5,70,90,95), yearly=TRUE)

Drought events

vmt_drought <- lfstat::vary_threshold(lf_flow,
                      varying="monthly",
                      fun=function(x){quantile(x, probs=c(0.2))})
